44":"about 1544","1616":"1616","1559":"1559","1526":"1526","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, England","Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Kent, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Kent, England":"Kent, England, United Kingdom","Thorpe, Norfolk, England":"Thorpe, Norfolk, England","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kelsey","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from North or South Kelsey in Lincolnshire, so named from an uncertain initial element (perhaps an Old English personal name with genitive <i>-es</i>) + Old English <i>ēg</i> ‘island’.","Possibly also an Americanized form of German <b>Gelzer</b>.","History: William Kelsey was one of the founders of Hartford, CT, in 1635 (coming from Cambridge, MA with Thomas Hooker)."],"variants":[{"name":"Kelsay","meanings":["Probably a variant of   Kelsey  ."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705205,"age":10,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":12,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":26,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":28,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":41,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Kelsey was born in 1559, in Thorpe, Norfolk, England, her father, Roger Kelsey, was 39 and her mother, Elizabeth Sutton, was 33. She married James Buck Jr. in 1575, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1616, in Lavenham, Suffolk, England, at the age of 57, and was buried in Lavenham, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"1559–1616":"1559–1616","1545–1599":"1545–1599","1547–Male":"1547–Surnud","1560–1623":"1560–1623","1570–1657":"1570–1657","1555–1657":"1555–1657","1590–1657":"1590–1657","1595–1646":"1595–1646","1520–Male":"1520–Surnud","1526–Female":"1526–Surnud","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1570":"1570","1590":"1590","1569":"1569","1646":"1646","1657":"1657","1547":"1547","1623":"1623","1600":"1600","1545":"1545","1555":"1555","1599":"1599","1587":"1587","1575":"1575","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","1595":"1595","about 1544":"umbes 1544","1616":"1616","1559":"1559","1526":"1526","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, England","Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thorpe, Norfolk, England":"Thorpe, Norfolk, England","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1559–1616":"1559–1616","1545–1599":"1545–1599","1547–Male":"1547–Kuollut","1560–1623":"1560–1623","1570–1657":"1570–1657","1555–1657":"1555–1657","1590–1657":"1590–1657","1595–1646":"1595–1646","1520–Male":"1520–Kuollut","1526–Female":"1526–Kuollut","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1570":"1570","1590":"1590","1569":"1569","1646":"1646","1657":"1657","1547":"1547","1623":"1623","1600":"1600","1545":"1545","1555":"1555","1599":"1599","1587":"1587","1575":"1575","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","1595":"1595","about 1544":"noin 1544","1616":"1616